// REQUIRES: hivmc-a5
//
// E2E compile test: RoPE kernel from triton-ascend Customer_Kernels.
// Without consumer-lookahead, UB-aware analyzer rejects pairwise merges
// causing PlanMemory to hit UB overflow. With depth-2 lookahead, the
// analyzer pulls in downstream consumers and the merged estimate fits.
//
// The test verifies no UB overflow occurs (the original bug).
// The compilation may succeed or fail downstream (depending on hivmc version),
// but the key assertion is absence of UB overflow.
//
// RUN: bishengir-compile %s -target=Ascend950PR_9589 -enable-hfusion-compile=true -enable-triton-kernel-compile=true -enable-vf-fusion -vf-fusion-mode=ub-aware-op -o %t > %t.out 2>&1 || true
// RUN: FileCheck %s < %t.out
//
// CHECK-NOT: ub overflow

